reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small, Efficient, Practical
reviews.reviewText: I read other reviews about how small this is and to me that was a bonus. Its an emergency kit after all and I gave it to my boss for Christmas. He is an avid hunter and fisherman and with all the other gear one usually carries in the great outdoors this light weight bag simply attaches to a backpack or gun case. If you are looking for a kit for your car, this is not practical and there are many other options for that purpose. Who needs fishing line in a broken down car? I got this on sale for $27 and I couldn't be happier. It isn't for daily use, it's an emergency kit, so if you keep that in mind before you purchase you should be happy with this bag.
